OL,3,CYorkshire Water fined #865k after
OL,4,Cpollution kills hundreds of fish
OL,6,FYorkshire Water has been fined
OL,7,F#865,000 after hundreds of fish died
OL,8,Fdue to pollution of a freshwater dike.
OL,10,FAbout a million litres of chlorinated
OL,11,Fwater a day was released into the
OL,12,Fdike, which flows out of Ingbirchworth
OL,13,FReservoir in Penistone, near Barnsley,
OL,14,Fover a four week period in 2017.
OL,16,FA local fisherman eventually alerted
OL,17,Fthe Environment Agency.
OL,19,FYorkshire Water pleaded guilty in
OL,20,FFebruary to one charge of polluting
OL,21,Fthe water.
